What happens with a different process model?¶


If instead we have quadratic decay to the steady state:

\begin{equation*} \dfrac{\textrm{d}T(t)}{\textrm{d}t}=-k\left(T(t) - T_a\right)^2, \end{equation*}

which has solution \begin{equation*} T(t)=\frac{kT_a(T_a-T(0))t-T(0)}{k(T_a-T(0))t-1}. \end{equation*}


Again, we assume that $T(0)$ is known (e.g. measurable) so that we infer two parameters

\begin{equation*} \theta=(T_{a},k)^\mathsf{T}. \end{equation*}
